â“ What additional information does Driver Details provide?

Answer:
Driver Details shows information about the virtual display driver used by VirtualBox, including driver file names, locations, and system components responsible for handling the virtual monitor. ğŸ“„ğŸ–¥ï¸

â“ What two options do you have for updating the driver?

Answer:

Search automatically for updated driver software

Browse my computer for driver software

These options allow Windows in VirtualBox to search online or use drivers installed locally in the virtual machine. ğŸŒğŸ› ï¸

â“ What does the Roll Back Driver button do? Why could it be grayed out?

Answer:
The Roll Back Driver button restores the previous version of a driver if the current one causes issues.
In a VirtualBox environment, this option may be grayed out because no previous driver version has been installed for the virtual device. â†©ï¸âš ï¸

